com.ibasco.agql.core

Interface Messenger<R extends AbstractRequest,S extends AbstractResponse>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable, ConfigurationSupport
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HttpMessenger, NettyMessenger

    public interface Messenger<R extends AbstractRequest,S extends AbstractResponse>
extends Closeable, ConfigurationSupport
    The following are characteristics/roles of a Messenger
    • Responsible for creating, acquiring, closing or releasing a network resource (e.g. Channel/Connection)
    • Prepares and initialize the request for Transport
    • Receives a response from the remote server, performs additional processing (if needed) and routes the response back to the Client
    • Has a 1 to 1 relationship with the Client
    Author:
    Rafael Luis Ibasco
